Description: Rim sherd of Attic, probably black-figured, pottery eye-cup; interior: reserved band at top of rim, glazed black below; top of lip glazed; exterior: narrow line near top of rim; below, near centre of sherd, painted decoration consisting of part of eyebrow above part of eye.
Curator's comments: For parallels, see New York, Metropolitan Museum 96.18.50.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0608) (Phase 1)
